parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust manifold studs can cause exhaust fumes to enter the passenger compartment, leading to potential health hazards and decreased vehicle control. Additionally, the failure can cause loud noises, decreased engine performance, and potentially lead to engine damage.
symptoms: Loud noises from the engine
exhaust fumes entering the passenger compartment
decreased engine performance
broken or sheared-off studs
and excessive exhaust leakage.
